text: Harvey Frick (October 13, 1893 - May 6, 1966) was an American long-distance runner. He competed in the marathon at the 1928 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1893 births Category:1966 deaths Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:American male long- distance runners Category:American male marathon runners Category:Olympic track and field athletes of the United States Category:Sportspeople from New York City Category:Track and field athletes from New York (state)
